Dear friends,

It is with great pride and joy that Idrefjällens OK welcome you all to Orienteering World Cup Idre Fjäll 2021. To be able to invite the greatest orienteers in the world is a great honour. The northwest part of the Swedish county Dalarna will offer both testing and exciting challenges whilst surrounded by the most gorgeous nature.

Watch the World Cup in Idre Fjall from IOF-LIVE

LIVE/Welcome: https://orienteering.sport/event/world-cup-round-2/welcome/

- August 12 Long distance 
– IOF-LIVE: https://orienteering.sport/event/world-cup-round-2/long/

- August 14 Middle distance
– IOF-LIVE: https://orienteering.sport/event/world-cup-round-2/middle/

- August 15 Relays
– IOF-LIVE: https://orienteering.sport/event/world-cup-round-2/relay/

Idrefjällens OK welcome you all to Idre Fjäll in the summer of 2021 and we promise to do our very best to provide and host an event that all of you, including runners, coaches, spectators, partners, sponsors, and media representatives will enjoy. We hope this event, Orienteering World Cup Idre Fjäll 2021 will give you all fond memories to look back on.

Booking of accommodation is open with discounted prices at Idre Fjall for all teams. Follow the link for accommodation.

A Covid-19 Bulletin World Cup Idre Fjäll has been published.

Information about Model Event map and Embargoed areas;

We have published a new map Embargoed areas on IOF Eventor. Also the map of the  Model event area is published.
We want you to notice that the road to Nipfjällsstugan (through Gammelsätervallen and the border line in the West of the Model Event map) is closed between 10am 11 August until 6pm 12 August 2021.
So, if you want to drop your athletes in the northern part of the Model Event area you have to do it before 10am 11 August 2021.
The road is open again from 6pm Thursday 12 August.
Printed Model Event maps will be received when entering Orienteering World Cup Idre Fjäll.

To add regarding Embargoed areas. At Gränjesåsvallen the embargoed area border must be followed. That means for example that the public parking lot Städjan is not allowed to use beacuse it is inside the embargoed area.

We have also provided films from all roads where you can see how it looks when driving the roads in our competition areas. 

Any questions;
Competition related; raceoffice@owc2021.se
Covid-19 related; covid@owc2021.se
General questions; info@owc2021.se


Welcome to Idre Fjäll and Sweden!

Idrefjällens OK

information:
Värska OK Peko announces that the Estonian Championships in middle and long distance orienteering will take place! (February 22-23 in Haanja).

The course setters have been working in the forest for two days, and the condition of the tracks ranges from poor to very good. There is little snow under dense spruce trees, while ski trails and open areas are in excellent condition. We are still fine-tuning the course planning and will provide updates on course lengths and other details as we go.

Registration is open until late Tuesday evening, February 18.
Entries must be made at https://www.control200.com/InfoEvento.aspx?Evento=289 . Organizers will register the entries in Eventor by the end of deadline.

Participants must register their entries here and also in duplicate via the OriOasis platform.
https://www.orioasis.pt/oasis/events.php?action=event_view_info&eventid=2926
